description.narrative: To (i) contribute to the reduction of transport costs and travel time along the Osh-Batken-Isfana road corridor; and (ii) improve road safety planning and road asset management; and (iii) repair and rehabilitate road infrastructure in and around Osh and Jalal-Abad cities thereby creating temporary jobs.

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, A.5 | Description :For the purposes of carrying out the Project, the Recipient shallcause MOTC to update in form and substance satisfactory to the Association, the Project Operational Manual. | Due Date :30-Dec-2010

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, A.6 | Description :For the purposes of carrying out Part A.2 of the Project, theRecipient shall, through MOTC enter into and thereafter maintain, implementation arrangements with the Municipality of Osh. | DueDate :31-Oct-2010
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, A3 | Description :The Recipient, through the MOTC, shall submit an Annual Work Programfor the following calendar year. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I., A | Description :The Recipient, through the MoTC, shall no later than June 1 of eachcalendar year, during the implementation of Part A of the Project, starting June 1, 2011. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I., A. | Description :The Recipient, through MoTC, shall no later than December 15 of eachcalendar year, during the implementation of the Project, starting December 15, 2009, submit to the Association an Annual Work Progr| Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I., A.4 | Description :The Recipient, through MoTC, shall no later than December 15 of eachcalendar year, during the implementation of the Project, starting December 15, 2011, submit to the Association an Annual Work Pro |Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I., A.5 | Description :The Recipient, shall, not later than June 1 of each calendar year,provide support for an independent audit and action on findings. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section II, A,.3 | Description :The Recipient shall furnish to the Association, a separate reportdescribing the status of implementation of each component of the Project and a summary report of Project implementation. | Due Date:15-Aug-2011

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section II, A.1 | Description :The Recipient shall monitor and evaluate the progress of the Projectand prepare Project Reports covering one calendar semester, within 45 days after end of period. | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section II, A.2 | Description :The Recipient shall carry out jointly with the Association, a midtermreview of the progress made in carrying out the Project. | Due Date :01-Sep-2011

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section II, B.2 | Description :The Recipient shall prepare and furnish to the Association interimunaudited financial reports for the Project covering the quarter, in form and substance satisfactory to the Association. |Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section IV, B.1 | Description :No withdrawal shall be made for payments made prior to the date ofthis Agreements, except that withdrawals up to an aggregate amount not to exceed SDR 1,200,000 out of the Grant may be made. | DueDate :31-Oct-2010

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section IV., B. | Description :Notwithstanding the provisions of Part A of this Section, nowithdrawal shall be made under category 1 unless the EMP and RAP have been prepared. | Due Date :26-Feb-2010
